data.meta_description:
17 likes, 3 comments - cookologyculinaryschool on May 20, 2024: "On Sunday, the anniversary of the death of Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis, the First Ladies Man and historian Andrew Och, spoke about Mrs. Kennedy’s influence on White House dining. 

Chef Patrick Vanas taught the class and began by teaching everyone how to make The Clint, a Negroni created by Jackie’s secret service agent. Then he taught Boula-Boula, turtle soup, using mock turtle soup! (No turtles were eaten!), and moved to her favorite Poulet a l’estragon (Tarragon Chicken), finally a Soufflé Froid du Chocolate, which is so very unlike how it is made today. Like a lot of dishes in the 60s-80s, gelatin was used in the chocolate soufflé. It was interesting. 

Join us for the next First Ladies Man class, on Mamie Eisenhower on Sunday,June 23.
